# Update Rules

## 0. Role Of This File

This file stores cross-doc cascade rules. Use it after {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}} results, method changes, operating-rule changes, and docs hierarchy changes.

## 1. {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}} Completion Cascade

When a {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}} finishes, update:

- `docs/project/project-status.md`: verdict and next task.
- `docs/project/themes/theme-index.md`: compact new {{ANALYSIS_RECORD_LABEL}} row.
- `docs/project/themes/theme-bodies.md`: detailed new {{ANALYSIS_RECORD_LABEL}} body.
- `docs/method/algorithmic-levers.md`: lever state.
- `docs/evaluation/comparison.md`: numeric column.
- `docs/project/backlog/README.md`: backlog.
- `docs/operations/session-kickoff.md`: next-session protocol.

## 2. Method And Terminology Cascade

Method changes cascade to `docs/method/` and `docs/evaluation/evaluation-and-visualization.md`.

New terminology goes to `docs/concepts/glossary.md`.

Startup-instruction changes require checking both `docs/entrypoint.md` and `docs/operations/project-memory-and-instructions.md`.

## 3. Operating Rule Cascade

New recurring constraints go to `docs/operations/rules/operational-constraints.md`.

New hard prohibitions go to `docs/operations/rules/forbidden-actions.md`.

New delivery checks go to `docs/operations/rules/deliverable-checklist.md`.

After any rules route change, update `docs/operations/shared-instructions.md`, `docs/operations/README.md`, and `docs/entrypoint.md` as needed.
